This project implements an automatic headlight control system using an STM32-based trainer kit. It uses an LDR (Light Dependent Resistor) to detect ambient light conditions and automatically switches the LED (headlight) ON or OFF. The system improves driver convenience, energy efficiency, and safety by eliminating the need for manual control.

🎯 Objectives
-To detect ambient light intensity using an LDR
-To process sensor data using STM32 microcontroller
-To automatically control vehicle headlights (LED)
-To implement a simple ON/OFF automation system
